  "description": "A short curriculum for reading poetry well, in roughly the order a new reader should take them.\nThe Line and the Break — why the line, not the sentence, is poetry\u0026rsquo;s basic unit. What Is Metrical Poetry — how a metrical poem keeps a bargain with the reader\u0026rsquo;s ear, and what distinguishes it from free verse. Sound and Meter — the toolkit of feet, substitutions, and sonic devices. Fixed Forms and the Sonnet — how meter combines with rhyme scheme and stanza pattern, with the sonnet as the worked example. ",
